highlights.description: Mark, a current member of WI state legislature, talks about his call to engage in public service
Carl talks about having the opportunity to listen to another person at the store during an ice storm, and having his eye's opened to another person's experience
Julie talks about visiting communities in Central Mexico in which women made $3/day selling flowers, and exuding pride about where they live
David expresses surprise about a gathering on Library Mall that consisted entirely of Black students
Julie talks about working with Habitat for Humanity, collecting loan payments, and observing the difficulty people have making mortgage payments
Julie talks about the difficulties posed by everyone wanting to have their own car
Betty talks about renting part of her home to a college student at below-market rates, and this being the only way this young woman could afford to live in Madison as a college student
Carl expresses hope about "middle-class and poor people" on the East side speaking up for themselves, school board candidates sticking up for their communities
Barbara talks about an asylum family no longer able to get their kids on BadgerCare
